OL,3,CCan Glasgow afford to continue
OL,4,Cwelcoming refugees?
OL,6,FThe historically pro-immigration
OL,7,Fcouncil is now warning that the rising
OL,8,Fnumbers and a lack of UK government
OL,9,Fsupport are placing extreme pressure
OL,10,Fon the city's housing and homelessness
OL,11,Fservices.
OL,13,FGlasgow has more asylum seekers than
OL,14,Fany other local authority in the UK.
OL,15,FOnce people are granted leave to
OL,16,Fremain and become refugees, they are
OL,17,Fno longer the responsibility of the
OL,18,FHome Office but of the council.
