OL,3,CCan Glasgow afford to continue
OL,4,Cwelcoming refugees?
OL,6,FScotland has more generous
OL,7,Fhomelessness laws than the rest of the
OL,8,FUK, which means Glasgow has a
OL,9,Fresponsibility to house every asylum
OL,10,Fseeker who becomes a refugee.
OL,12,FThis pressure has pushed the city into
OL,13,Fa housing emergency.
OL,15,FMore than half of those in temporary
OL,16,Faccommodation are now refugees.
OL,18,FUnprecedented numbers of new refugees
OL,19,Fare also now travelling from other
OL,20,Fcities to Glasgow - because they know
OL,21,Fit is their best hope for a home.
